sentence: Energy stocks were ending slightly lower this afternoon with the NYSE Energy Sector Index slipping 0.1% while shares of energy companies in the S&P 500 were down less than 0.1% as a group.
Crude oil for May delivery settled $2.22 higher at $51.43 per barrel while May natural gas futures fell 5 cents to $2.67 per 1 million BTU.

In company news, TransGlobe Energy Corp (TGA,TGL.TO) rose Thursday after the Canadian oil and natural gas producer today announced the start of a normal course issuer bid for up to 6.2 million of its common shares, equal to around 10% of its public float.
TGA shares were ahead nearly 3% in late trade at $3.62 each, backing down from an earlier run to $3.97 a share.
The stock has traded within a 52-week range of $2.67 to $8.28 a share, falling nearly 57% over the past year prior to today's price gain.
TGL.TO shares were up slightly more than 2% at C$4.50 apiece at the Toronto Stock Exchange, earlier climbing to a session high of C$4.90 a share.

(-) LPG, Gives back initial initial gains that followed the liquefied petroleum gas shipping company announcing April 1 start for an eight-ship pool of very large gas carriers with a Singapore-based subsidiary of Mitsui OSK Lines Ltd.

(-) FF, Procter & Gamble ( PG ) tells biofuels company it plans to end its purchase agreement on Dec. 31.
The bio-fuels company received $43.9 million in revenue during 2014 from PG, representing 12.8% of its total revenue.
